What types of dresses are recommended for summer?What types of dresses are recommended for summer?
Some types of dresses recommended for summer include halter dresses, tube dresses, and sundresses. Halter dresses offer the benefit of an open-back design ideal for warm weather, while tube dresses feature a strapless design. Meanwhile, sundresses offer the benefits of being lightweight and comfortable, making them ideal for summer.
read more
What does "halter" mean when buying a dress?What does "halter" mean when buying a dress?
A halter dress is typically a type of dress without a back. The dress is also often sleeveless and is secured behind the neck and at the waist.
read more
halter dress
How to choose the right dress length to buy?How to choose the right dress length to buy?
The length your dress should be will depend on the type of dress you get. For example, most maxi dresses are designed to go to just above your ankles, and midi dresses are designed to reach down to your shin.
read more
What types of dresses are recommended for casual occasions?What types of dresses are recommended for casual occasions?
The dresses that are considered casual are typically shorter in length. Some popular shorter dresses are mini dresses and knee-length dresses.
read more
What's the difference between a maxi dress and a midi dress?What's the difference between a maxi dress and a midi dress?
The difference between a midi dress and a maxi dress is the length. A midi dress stretches down to just below the knee or to the lower calf. A maxi dress is longer and will typically reach the ankles or the floor.
